title: I’ve returned to Etsy
body:
My shop: https://www.etsy.com/shop/CreationsByChaosfay

Artyah decided to just…vanish.  Their server isn’t connecting or something.  I haven’t even been able to contact customer service because the email address is no longer valid.  No idea what’s going on. 

So I’ve moved back to Etsy.  I checked out several other sites, but none fit as well as Etsy.  When I’m making at least $100/month (a girl can dream!) I’ll look into having a site custom made for me. 

If you’d rather not use Etsy and are more comfortable with a PayPal invoice, please contact me directly.  I can set that up quite easily and have done so for many commissions and multi-payments. 

BTW, I have a coupon code active now.  Use SPRINGBACK for 25% off a purchase of $100 or more; expires April 14, 2019.

Cacoa is my current mood.

summary: I’m making this for my college best friend and I want to challenge myself to go out and physically Mail this thing because I get...
body:
I’m making this for my college best friend and I want to challenge myself to go out and physically Mail this thing because I get so much anxiety about using the mail (physical or electronic). It’s mostly usually either just bills or spam and I was supposed to send my friend something last year that she left behind here and I never did and now I worry that it’s too late because it was her daughter’s and maybe her daughter outgrew it?

I want to make a bunch of oil pastel pieces actually, because I want to use up more of my art supplies. I have plenty of sketchbooks and tools. And I want to sell the stuff I make because I’m not as attached to it as I am to my oil paintings.

But this one is for my friend who taught me how to appreciate music better and deepened my love for it and who taught me to look at and love the moon. We spent so many nights on my balcony talking about an endless array of topics and she would always say “look at the moon!” And it really is a wonderful object floating in space, reflecting the light of the sun, totally affecting our moods using the same forces that pull the ocean waters to create currents.

This isn’t done yet but I thought I’d share the progress so far. I haven’t been the most responsible today but making art makes me feel better and less mentally jumbled and tangled up.

I was also thinking today about what emotions drove me to these compulsive actions as a means of coping, and how maybe I wouldn’t get to such states if I were more disciplined in how often I create. It’s just wild because I work with so many mediums. If I were rich I would hire an assistant whose job it would be exclusively (and nothing else) to listen and help me bounce ideas for planning my time and then making sure I follow my schedule (especially the part where I need to stop doing something even if I’m in the zone, and to keep me from posting on social media in unstructured ways). Basically I would hire them to be my structure enforcer/encourager.

But I think it’s nice that when I’m upset I create beautiful things to make myself feel better.
